Dialogue: 10,0:01:32.36,0:01:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, we finally held \Na great midnight feast.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.25,0:01:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It was fun! And the food tastes better \Nin the middle of the night!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.53,0:01:41.33,Top,,0,0,0,,Doris' clown dance was a sight to behold too. {???????? no clue what's that kenzaka}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:41.33,0:01:44.57,Top,,0,0,0,,I panicked, wondering what would happen \Nwhen Miss Kennedy came.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.57,0:01:46.49,Top,,0,0,0,,I was relieved when she said she won't report it.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:46.49,0:01:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Pat... \NSomething is worrying me about Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.68,0:01:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, she's doing jolly well. \NShe's a lot more cheerful now.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:53.58,0:01:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And she was put on the lacrosse team with you!
Dialogue: 10,0:01:56.00,0:01:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. As the school's representatives, \Nwe've gotta do our best!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.63,0:02:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{??}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.05,0:02:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.32,0:02:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that feeling earlier, and use it during the match to stop St. Christopher’s shots.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.39,0:02:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.39,0:02:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm putting you out as our goalkeeper. Got it? {we hear goalie but it's goalkeeper in book}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:38.81,0:02:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? There's no way I'm fit for that yet. \NIf you picked a second-former...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.31,0:02:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Don’t worry. Of all our players, you’re the quickest to intercept a ball, as long as you stay calm. {??}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.77,0:02:50.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly! Be more confident, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:51.64,0:02:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:55.91,0:02:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh geez, I'm exhausted...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:58.68,0:03:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Isabel. \NLet's get up early tomorrow and practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:02.25,0:03:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There are only three days to the match.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.98,0:03:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Early in the morning? \NI don't know if I'll be able to...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.10,0:03:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wake you up. \NWe're the only first-formers on the team.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:09.36,0:03:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't afford an embarrassing match, can we?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:11.79,0:03:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're right. \NWe must do our best.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.79,0:03:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.72,0:03:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.28,0:03:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll all be there to cheer you on, \Nso give them a proper hiding! {https://www.phrases.org.uk/meanings/a-good-hiding.html}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:18.28,0:03:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure. But St. Christopher’s has a strong team.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.14,0:03:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If only, only I could shoot \Ntwo or three goals on Saturday... {b}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.01,0:03:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.38,0:03:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You said it again, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.38,0:03:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder who it was who turned her nose up
Dialogue: 10,0:03:35.62,0:03:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,at lacrosse just a few weeks ago, \Nsaying it’s nothing but hockey in the air?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:39.77,0:03:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Who vowed and declared she would never try \Nto be any good at a silly game like lacrosse?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.13,0:03:50.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have seemed rather an idiot... {b}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.63,0:03:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were a bit of a goof. \NDo you know what we used to call you back then?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.44,0:03:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The stuck-up twins!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:57.24,0:03:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! What a dreadful name...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:59.87,0:04:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.71,0:04:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What dreadful name?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:05.58,0:04:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:09.53,0:04:12.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right... \NI'm going to shine in that match!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.65,0:04:17.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,If I become the pride of our form, \Nthey'll surely forget that silly nickname sooner.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:41.01,0:04:44.79,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dad, Mum, we're doing more or less fine so far. {if this is a letter, should we close it in the quotation marks?}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:44.79,0:04:47.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,Isabel is giving her all \Nat lacrosse practice right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.89,0:04:52.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,She was picked for a guest match. \NIt stings, but she even beat me!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.43,0:04:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,"There will be a match on Saturday. \NPlease pray that we win. {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.43,0:04:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel will write to you soon with the results.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:59.40,0:05:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, that's all. \N—Pat."
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.83,0:05:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, that's all?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.39,0:05:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That sounds like Pat.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.04,0:05:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'm glad they're doing well.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:08.31,0:05:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,They've finally managed to adjust, it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.51,0:05:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They must've realized \Nwhy St. Clare's is the best for them. {lit: understood the goodness of clare}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:13.35,0:05:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need to worry anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.87,0:05:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I want to believe... {/good if so}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:17.52,0:05:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The match is today.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.19,0:05:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel must be working hard right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.79,0:05:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's prepare for the welcoming luncheon!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.39,0:05:29.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And make haste, the St. Christopher’s players will be arriving soon!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:30.26,0:05:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, what's on the menu today?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:33.57,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Sausages, mashed potatoes, and pudding.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:36.82,0:05:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! I wonder if there’ll be seconds. {lit: let's ask for refill}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.34,0:05:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Overeating won't do!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.78,0:05:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You too, Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:42.88,0:05:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want both of you to give it your best \Nand become the pride of the first form.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:47.28,0:05:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep. Instead, we ought to make sure \Nthe other team eats so much they can’t stand.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:51.05,0:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one pudding, though.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:54.82,0:05:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you win, the whole form \Nwill stand you cream-buns at tea-time! {b, “stand you cream-buns” is old-fashioned British slang meaning treat you to cream-buns (buy them for you).}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:11.76,0:06:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, you had a midnight feast? \NI'm jealous!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.31,0:06:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you commute from home, \Nyou don't get to have that kind of fun.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.61,0:06:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,More sausages, anyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:21.75,0:06:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.38,0:06:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, what's your \Nlacrosse team like this year?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:26.12,0:06:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve beaten you each time \Nwe’ve played you so far.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:28.17,0:06:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't mind if we allow ourselves \Nto beat you again today.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:33.18,0:06:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! Make sure to catch their shots, \Nfor a cream-buns treat!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.37,0:06:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One bun per shot stopped!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.48,0:06:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,M-My heart is pounding... \NWhat should I do?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.18,0:06:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry. \NJust do what we always do.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:59.92,0:07:02.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,Kathleen is completely untroubled by this. {/very calm}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:02.99,0:07:06.14,Thought,,0,0,0,,She’s like a completely different person \Nfrom when we first met her.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:06.14,0:07:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, Isabel, don't hold back!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:09.73,0:07:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,New goalkeeper? {?????? no clue what's that first word, eda or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.23,0:07:14.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? She seems rather small. {meaning the size of her body}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.18,0:07:16.09,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a first-former. \NI wonder if she'll manage.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.54,0:07:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{?}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.51,0:07:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, don't mind the seniors! \NJust give it your all!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:49.95,0:07:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking good, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.40,0:08:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicely done, Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.95,0:08:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that up!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:17.41,0:08:19.38,Note,,0,0,0,,{LMAO Im not changing the rest of "Christopher's" to this}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.36,0:08:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, we're still in good shape. \NI'm sure you can turn it around in the second half.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:55.77,0:08:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone on the other team is so fast, \Nit's almost impossible to keep up!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.44,0:09:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, why don't you try \Nshooting some goals now? {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.31,0:09:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.93,0:09:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When you see an opening, \Nshoot with all your might—just like in practice.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.86,0:09:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.05,0:09:10.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, I missed three goals already... {lit: let them take 3 points}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.37,0:09:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We could use those three extra points, \Nbut you also saved four, didn't you? {???  think she means "it'd be even better without those three points for the other team"}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.77,0:09:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go! {iku wa yo}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.52,0:09:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.37,0:09:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Isabel! \NKeep that up and we'll turn it around! {???}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.95,0:09:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s it! You’ve levelled the score! {???? guessing}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.56,0:09:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,C'mon, hurry! {????}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.77,0:10:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, you... {kono}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.67,0:10:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?! {nani sunna yo}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.61,0:10:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, you can do it! \NWe need this one extra point!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.03,0:10:18.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel! Shoot now!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.11,0:10:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She did it!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:24.57,0:10:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Nicely done, Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.58,0:10:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Cream-buns are yours!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:30.05,0:10:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.07,0:10:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, you both did extremely well.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:39.34,0:10:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the pride of our first form!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:41.91,0:10:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet went to buy the cream-buns for you. \NLook forward to it!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.30,0:10:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong? \NWe thought you went to town. {lit: didn't you go shopping}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.27,0:10:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't buy the cream-buns.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:57.92,0:10:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My money is gone.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.58,0:11:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.19,0:11:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I definitely had five shillings on me \Njust this morning.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.00,0:11:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I went to buy the cream-buns, \NI couldn't find them!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:07.55,0:11:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's weird.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:08.94,0:11:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I also lost my ten shillings the other day...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.60,0:11:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's Janet?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.51,0:11:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NHurry up, we've gotta prepare the tea.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:17.91,0:11:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The day-girls of St. Christopher’s are waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:21.25,0:11:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... I was so looking forward \Nto those cream-buns....
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.19,0:11:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, take this. {/buy it with this}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:28.19,0:11:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! We wanted to buy them for you and Isabel \Nbecause you did so well in the match.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:32.84,0:11:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do use this. \NWe're also grateful to you all.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:36.00,0:11:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Your support is what kept us going—\Nit's what allowed us to win! Right, Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.03,0:11:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Y-Yeah...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.02,0:11:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Janet, Kathleen is doing it with all her heart, \Nso you should accept it. {lit: because it's the precious feelings of kathleen, accept}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:45.64,0:11:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thank you, Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.84,0:11:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be on my way, then!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:51.50,0:11:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How jolly generous our Kathleen is!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:55.28,0:11:57.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Kathleen... Please tell me I'm wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:11.46,0:12:16.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,When Janet couldn’t find her money, \Nwe gave up on trying those cream-buns.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.67,0:12:20.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,But thanks to Kathleen, \Nshe was able to buy enough for everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:23.29,0:12:26.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,We had a great time chatting with the day-girls
Dialogue: 10,0:12:26.13,0:12:32.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,from St. Christopher's, and we sent them off \Nsaying we look forward to playing them again.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:38.69,0:12:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done, both of you.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.69,0:12:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Your early morning practice paid off.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.96,0:12:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You ought to make that into a habit. {lit: that attitude/posture is very important}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.68,0:12:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.42,0:12:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, come here for a second.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.07,0:12:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.33,0:12:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.65,0:13:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I heard.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.18,0:13:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel, you lost money too?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.98,0:13:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh? Yeah... Two shillings, \Nright before our midnight feast.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.99,0:13:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you leave it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:08.20,0:13:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In my wallet, in the top drawer of my nightstand.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.17,0:13:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So someone really did steal them!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:13.16,0:13:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like the ten shillings from my drawer, \Nand the five shillings from Janet's coat.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.00,0:13:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... Belinda Towers told me \Nsome of her money was gone too.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.20,0:13:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there can be no doubt—we have a thief!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:23.80,0:13:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the girls? {lit: St. Clare's student?}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:24.91,0:13:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course not! \NHow could one of us do it?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:27.06,0:13:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It would've been plausible \Nif we had any outsiders wandering around. {???, im told "had had" is more correct, but I am going to leave it as is since this sounds more casual}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.64,0:13:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The culprit is right here, in our school!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.68,0:13:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's tell Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.92,0:13:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not be hasty! {lit: saying something like it's criminal! - meaning "don't jump to conclusions"}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.85,0:13:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the money that I lost \Nmay have been simply misplaced. {lit: my money that's gone may have been a mistake/misunderstanding}{♪ if you look for a knife or a fork and you think it is merely misplaced ♪}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:42.29,0:13:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But mine was definitely stolen! \NI'm sure I still had those ten shillings on me.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.48,0:13:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time something like this happens, \Nlet's report it to Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:50.91,0:13:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, everyone, \Nbe careful with your money.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:54.40,0:13:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Take every precaution so it doesn’t get stolen.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.77,0:14:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Isabel? \NIt's almost dinner time.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.82,0:14:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important, and it won't take long!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:03.31,0:14:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Something about Kathleen? {sounds like question so probably comes from pat}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.79,0:14:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What? It can't be! {/no way I can't believe it}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:07.78,0:14:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't want to believe it either.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:10.28,0:14:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But when you think about it, \Nit was when everyone’s money
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.12,0:14:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,began disappearing that Kathleen became \Nso generous and extravagant.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:16.46,0:14:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't she just receive \Npocket money from her dad?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:19.86,0:14:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I also thought at first...
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.96,0:14:24.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I really fancy Kathleen as she is these days—
Dialogue: 10,0:14:24.90,0:14:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so kind to everyone, always going about \Nwith that can-do attitude.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:28.77,0:14:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So do I! That's why I haven't told you before.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:32.37,0:14:34.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to doubt others—I really do!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.19,0:14:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If... If that's true, we ought \Nto tell Kathleen to stop doing that.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.81,0:14:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't just make such an outrageous claim... {lit: until we know for sure, we can't say that}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.68,0:14:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I really hope I'm just wrong.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:43.55,0:14:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah... Let's not discuss it with the others for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.64,0:14:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. And also keep an eye on Kathleen.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.56,0:15:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Isabel! Gym class is starting. \NYou'll be late if you don't go now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:01.95,0:15:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?! It's that late already?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.89,0:15:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We've only five minutes left. Hurry up!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:06.12,0:15:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no! But what should I do? \NKathleen hasn't come back yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:10.08,0:15:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did she go?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.31,0:15:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To the room of Rita George, \Nhead of the Nature Club in sixth form. {we hear "jones" but it's "george" in book}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.08,0:15:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go remind her!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.36,0:15:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, please forgive me! \NOh, please don’t tell anyone! {b}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:27.94,0:15:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.98,0:15:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that a student of St. Clare's \Nwould stoop to this!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:31.88,0:15:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I must report this to Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.54,0:15:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dismissed. Leave now!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:42.49,0:15:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:55.51,0:15:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen! What happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:56.89,0:15:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We can talk if you want to...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.96,0:16:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Go away! \NDon’t come prying after me. {lit: leave me alone}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.01,0:16:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't leave you. \NWe're your friends, you know.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.83,0:16:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You’d be horrified to be friends with me \Nif I told you what had happened.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:08.82,0:16:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, you were the very first friend \Nwe made when we came to St. Clare’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:13.34,0:16:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll be our friend forever, \Nno matter what.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:16.24,0:16:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever’s happened? Tell us!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.96,0:16:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’ll tell you—and you can go \Nand spread it all round the school if you like— {b}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.05,0:16:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and everyone can laugh and jeer at me—
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.85,0:16:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,but I’ll not be here by then!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.69,0:16:33.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen, please don't talk like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.99,0:16:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We won’t turn on you, I promise.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:36.46,0:16:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you will!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.26,0:16:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What I’ve done is so dreadful!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:41.48,0:16:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You won’t believe it! \NI hardly believe it myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:45.97,0:16:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m a thief!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:47.87,0:16:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I took all the money that’s been missing!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.91,0:16:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Even your two shillings, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:51.82,0:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hillary's, Janet's, and Belinda's money—all of it!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.11,0:16:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.98,0:16:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:59.28,0:17:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a mother.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:01.42,0:17:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven’t anyone to send me money and sweets \Nall the time like you and the other girls have. {b}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:05.86,0:17:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But didn't you say before...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:07.01,0:17:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That was all a lie.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.16,0:17:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The only truth is that my father is away abroad.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.20,0:17:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,But he’s so busy that he had to leave me \Nin the care of my old aunt.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:16.17,0:17:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:17.04,0:17:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Aunt only gives me about a penny a week!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:19.91,0:17:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,One penny?! That's all?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:22.44,0:17:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,She says you don't need money \Nto live in the common dorm.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.24,0:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But what can you do with just a single penny—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.68,0:17:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,buy a friend a present, give at church, \Nor get your everyday little things?!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.38,0:17:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Poor Kathleen...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.02,0:17:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurt so much to pretend I didn’t notice \Neveryone calling me stingy.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:37.49,0:17:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I really wanted to be generous to everyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:40.16,0:17:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to have friends.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.09,0:17:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day, I found a shilling \Nin the school yard.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.67,0:17:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The one shilling I needed to contribute \Nto the present for Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:50.04,0:17:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was such a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.50,0:17:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It even made Janet see me differently! {/change her mind about me}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:53.97,0:17:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So now I felt like I had to gift Janet \Nsomething nice for her birthday.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:00.50,0:18:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I still don't know why I did that...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:03.08,0:18:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But it made me so happy to see her delighted face... \NAnd then I could no longer stop... {lit: One after the other}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:10.39,0:18:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that'd make everyone happy, \Nbut I was just fooling myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:15.63,0:18:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A theft is a theft!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.46,0:18:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end, I just wanted \Nto force everyone to like me... {lit: but in the end I wanted to see myself well - think she means "be viewed in good light"; unsure tho, yoku can also be "greed" ????}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:21.87,0:18:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What a blithering idiot I've been!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.90,0:18:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So today, in Rita's room too...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.80,0:18:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.64,0:18:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So she’s going to tell Headmistress now,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.78,0:18:34.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and I shall be known all over the school as a thief, \Nand I’ll be expelled and...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.91,0:18:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.12,0:18:37.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please go!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.32,0:18:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Leave me alone. \NI need to pack up my things.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.69,0:18:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:40.82,0:18:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't bother! I know that in your heart of hearts \Nyou despise me too. Just leave me alone!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:45.12,0:18:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true, and never will be!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.11,0:18:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just leave... Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.86,0:19:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go and find Rita if we can! \NAsk her not to report it.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.29,0:19:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,She's probably in Headmistress's office. {already}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:04.02,0:19:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:14.45,0:19:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she report it already? {/talked to principal}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.93,0:19:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, come in.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.70,0:19:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Patricia and Isabel?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.63,0:19:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to ask you for a favor—\Nit's about Kathleen!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:32.12,0:19:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, what Kathleen did was awful. \NBut she's terribly upset about it now! {/regrets is very much now}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:37.31,0:19:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But oh, Headmistress, \NKathleen didn’t spend a penny on herself.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.88,0:19:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She took our money, \Nbut we got it back in gifts and things. {lit: we got it back in other form}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.63,0:19:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen isn’t an ordinary, \Ncontemptible kind of thief.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:47.59,0:19:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But if she gets sent away now, she may really \Nbecome one, and be spoilt for always! {/expelled}{b}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.92,0:19:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Please give her a chance!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.63,0:19:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m quite sure Kathleen would apologise to everyone, \Nand try to repay every penny to set it right.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:58.16,0:20:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we would help her in any way we could!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:01.97,0:20:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Headmistress!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.12,0:20:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hadn’t heard your story, \NI’d have had to judge based solely on Rita’s.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.08,0:20:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I might have written to her aunt \Nto take her away.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.55,0:20:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I dread what might have happened \Nto her, poor, sensitive child!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.29,0:20:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Headmistress! \NDo you mean that you will let Kathleen stay? {/will not expel}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:23.96,0:20:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I must talk to her first.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.63,0:20:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall know how to deal with her, don’t worry.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:29.30,0:20:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is she now?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.81,0:20:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,In her dormitory, packing.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.97,0:20:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Kathleen slipped up, \Nit can happen to anyone.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.36,0:20:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially when you're young.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.24,0:20:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What matters is what she does next.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.78,0:20:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have been watching over her warmly—\NI am proud of you both.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:49.22,0:20:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You are kind and understanding, \Ntwo things that matter a great deal.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:53.15,0:20:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, off to your lesson, and tell your teacher to excuse you for being late, since you’ve been with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.09,0:21:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I will also ask Rita not to let this story get around. \NYou two will keep it secret too, won’t you?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.33,0:21:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.10,0:21:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Headmistress.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.07,0:21:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky is stunning!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:13.64,0:21:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like my feelings right now!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.99,0:21:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it great that everything ended well?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:18.41,0:21:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone was kind enough to forgive you.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:21.18,0:21:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all thanks to you two.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.85,0:21:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And Headmistress too!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.43,0:21:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a wonderful person, \Njust like our mum said!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.72,0:21:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,She’s going to write to my aunt and ask for a proper amount of pocket money to be paid to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.96,0:21:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that great?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:35.26,0:21:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll be able to pay back all the money \Nand soon be generous again.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.53,0:21:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you can’t, just admit it frankly—\Ndon’t try to force yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:42.57,0:21:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:45.20,0:21:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad they didn't send you away! \NYou're our dear friend, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:49.46,0:21:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're mine! I'm a really lucky girl \Nto have wonderful friends like you two!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:55.88,0:21:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you be able to trust me again?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.32,0:21:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course we will!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.62,0:22:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because then we'll be able to store our fortunes with you—not the bank. {lit: if anything, we'll trust you with all our savings from the bank ; book went: “Of course we’ll trust you,” said Pat. “If you go on like that I’ll get a hundred pounds out of the bank and ask you to keep it for me! Don’t be such a silly-billy!”}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.52,0:22:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Pat, you silly-billy!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:08.76,0:22:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so lucky to be at St. Clare's!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:11.66,0:22:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I love this school!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.70,0:22:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Me too!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.35,0:23:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Pat!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.26,0:23:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.26,0:23:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, listen, Isabel.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:39.55,0:23:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Kennedy might soon resign.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.50,0:23:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Why? First time I'm hearing of that!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:44.02,0:23:46.49,Default,,0,0,0,,She says she's just not good at teaching.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.49,0:23:49.81,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true! \NMiss Kennedy is a wonderful teacher.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.81,0:23:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,She's, kind, sympathetic, and excellent!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.54,0:23:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.32,0:23:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But if Miss Kennedy really quits, \Nwhat are we going to do?!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:58.47,0:24:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time on Twins at St. Clare's:
Dialogue: 10,0:24:00.22,0:24:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay Strong, Miss Kennedy! {in book it's "Miss Kennedy Again"}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.22,0:24:04.74,Note,,0,0,0,,Episode 7 \NStay Strong, Miss Kennedy! {がんばれ! ケネディ先生}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.87,0:24:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it!
